description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Fellow F2 equivalent in Emergency Medicine (A&amp;E)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Worcestershire Acute Hospitals NHS Trust is looking for enthusiastic and committed Clinical Fellows in Emergency Medicine (A&amp;E) to work as part of our dynamic Emergency Medicine team based at the Alexandra Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alexandra Hospital (The Alex) is one of two Emergency Departments within the Trust, the other being the Worcestershire Royal Hospital. The two departments work together to provide Emergency care to the population of Worcestershire and surrounding areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking Emergency Medicine (A&amp;E) doctors who are passionate about delivering high quality urgent and emergency care. The Emergency Department team are flexible and supportive of each other and opportunities are available for doctors to develop their skills. The department has both a junior and a senior middle grade rota and the successful applicant will be joining the junior rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Emergency Department at the The Alex has over 55,000 attendances per year. The department has a Minor Injuries area staffed by ENPs as well as a full range of support staff including alcohol and mental health workers. Main inpatient specialties at the Alex include Acute and Specialty Medicine, Urology and Trauma &amp; Orthopaedics. The Worcestershire Royal Hospital provides a full range of inpatient services including Vascular Surgery and inpatient ENT and Maxillofacial Surgery. It also offers the countywide Hyperacute Stroke Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Worcestershire is a beautiful county with stunning recreational facilities and top rated schools. It is an excellent place to live and work with something for everyone. Worcester was voted the 28th happiest place to live in the UK in 2019 and Worcester enjoys good ever improving connections by road and rail to Birmingham, the South West and London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interested applicants should contact Mr Abdul Jalil, A&amp;E Clinical Lead via 01527 503030&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
